Package: OpenRI
Type: Package
Title: Supporting genomics research leveraging multimodal gene-centered regulatory interactions
Version: 1.0.0
Date: 2023-6-26
Authors@R: c(person("Hai", "Fang", email="fh12355@rjh.com.cn", role=c("aut","cre")))
Maintainer: Hai Fang <fh12355@rjh.com.cn>
Depends: R (>= 4.2.0), igraph, ggplot2
Imports: BiocGenerics, dplyr, forcats, GenomicRanges, ggnetwork, ggrepel, IRanges, magrittr, Matrix, methods, osfr, purrr, readr, stats, stringr, tibble, tidyr, XML, pbapply, curl, ggraph
Suggests: coin, foreach, ggridges, grid, gridExtra, RColorBrewer, rtracklayer, Gviz, MASS, dnet, graphics, grDevices, S4Vectors, utils, ggbio, GenomeInfoDb, doParallel, scales, data.tree, jsonlite
Description: This package builds on an open and scalable resource called 'OpenRI' for gene-centered regulatory interactions inclusive of non-coding genomic regions. As a backend for the web-server 'OpenRI', it enables interactive exploration of multimodal regulatory interactions (e/pQTL, promoter capture Hi-C, and enhancer-gene maps) and their use in epi/genomics research.
